01:09:15,880 --> 01:09:17,074
Hold up, guv.

567
01:09:25,320 --> 01:09:26,389
Wait here.

568
01:10:05,160 --> 01:10:06,718
WOMAN: Why don't you sit down?

569
01:10:15,080 --> 01:10:16,911
It's so hot in here.

570
01:10:17,480 --> 01:10:19,277
Take off your boots.

571
01:10:37,800 --> 01:10:41,349
I have to get back. I promised her.

572
01:10:41,440 --> 01:10:43,556
To put things right.

573
01:10:43,640 --> 01:10:47,713
And she loves me. She's waiting for me.

574
01:10:48,240 --> 01:10:49,514
(ARTILLERY FIRING)

575
01:10:49,880 --> 01:10:51,677
(EXPLOSION)

576
01:10:51,760 --> 01:10:52,749
Oi!

577
01:10:55,960 --> 01:10:57,075
Wait, wait, wait.

578
01:10:58,200 --> 01:11:01,158
Hey, what have you done with your boots?

579
01:11:03,680 --> 01:11:06,194
-Look, you're sure you're feeling all right?
-Never better.

580
01:11:06,280 --> 01:11:10,159
Now I'm wondering whether the beach
really is the best place for dinner.

581
01:11:10,240 --> 01:11:11,673
(BOMB EXPLODING)

582
01:11:11,760 --> 01:11:16,595
-I'm not sure, I don't recognise it.
-Dunno.

583
01:11:16,680 --> 01:11:18,796
-This'll do, down here.
-No.

584
01:11:19,880 --> 01:11:22,348
-No, no, it's further on.
-What is?

585
01:11:22,440 --> 01:11:24,556
This place I know, an old cottage
with white clapboards

586
01:11:24,640 --> 01:11:27,108
and blue-painted window frames.

587
01:11:28,920 --> 01:11:32,799
Aw, yes.
